column6: b'CHARDONNAY IGT TOSCANA 2018 Variety: chardonnay grapes Vinification and aging: Harvested by hand. Direct pres of whole bunches in pneumatic press. Low temperature juice racking and spontaneous fermentation. Fermentation and aging on fine lees for at least 4 months in French oak barrels. TASTING NOTES Colour: Brilliant pale straw. Notes: Enveloping, complex and refreshing nose, with notes of white flowers and vanilla. Fruitiness of peach with an elegant aroma of graphite. Palate: On the palate there is an explosion of brightness with an optimum acidity and body. The finishis full of flavor, fruity and mineral. Sustainable wine. *Must be 21 to purchase'

column6: b'Variety: Co-fermentation of Sangiovese grapes and a small amount of white grapes (Trebbiano and Vermentino). Vinification and aging: First the grapes are harvested with great care by hand. Then depending on the vintage a portion of the Rose goes through a longer maceration (2-12 hours according to the vintage); Then the grapes are soft pressed with gentle pneumatic press. The racking of the juice is always done at low temperatures and then the fermentation is spontaneous. Finally it\xe2\x80\x99s aged at least for 4 months on fine lees, then clarified and filtered. TASTING NOTES Color: Soft rose, hues of mango, and grapefruit. Notes: Crisp and refreshing on the nose, with notes of wild roses, raspberries and melon with a fading aroma of cream. Palate: Luscious, refreshing and enjoyable with well-balanced acidity. Fresh fruit on the finish. Sustainable wine. *Must be 21 to purchase'

column4:

column6: b'SANGIOVESE IGT TOSCANA Variety: Sangiovese grapes. Vinification and aging: Harvested by hand. Hand selected and de-stemmed. Spontaneous fermentation with controlled temperature in concrete and stainless steel vats. Maceration time depending on the years. Spontaneous malolactic fermentation. Aging in wood for 12 months (botti and barriques). Gentle filtered before bottling. TASTING NOTES Color: Ruby red. Notes: Intense and fragrant. Floral notes of violet and iris. Fruity notes of cherry and blackberry. Spicy notes of vanilla and pepper. Palate: Juicy, round and fresh. Good persistence. Sustainable wine. *Must be 21 to purchase'

column6: b'PROSECCO DOC EXTRA DRY, VENETO The star-bright straw yellow hue and lingering streams of tiny bubbles usher in subtle aromatics of flowers with pear and peach-like white -fleshed fruits.
